sentences: Unified Theory began to form in early 1998.
Unified Theory was originally called Luma, they issued a four-track CD through their website in 1999.
In August 2000 the band issued their self-titled debut album.
The group played a reunion show on August 4, 2010 at the King King in Hollywood.
section: == Unified Theory == | === Brief Reformation & Reunion Show ===

sentences: On March 12, 2012, it was revealed that Chris would be the new lead singer of the rock band Live.
He played the band's dress rehearsal show to a hometown crowd at the Strand-Capitol Theater in York, PA, on March 12, 2012.
He toured with the band and sang on the band's well received 2014 album The Turn.
On December 12, 2016, Live announced that original lead singer Ed Kowalczyk had returned to the band, though no reference was made to Shinn in the announcement.
From March 2012 to December 2016, he was the lead singer of the band Live.
He was previously the lead singer of the band Unified Theory.
After they were signed to Universal Records later that year, they changed their name to Unified Theory after the theory Albert Einstein was working on when he died.
Unified Theory has recently filmed a music video for the song "15 Hits", a song set to be released on their upcoming album.
